23/10/2002
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The UN's "human development index" ranked the Balkan countries in the middle of 173 countries included in a report published Tuesday (22 October). Croatia occupied 48th place, followed by Bulgaria (62nd), Romania (63rd), Macedonia (65th) and Albania (92nd). UN officials who presented the report in Sofia focused on significant regional disparities in income levels and recommended that Bulgaria promote policies aimed at uniform income distribution before joining the EU. (24 Chasa, Pari - 23/10/02; Novinite, BTA - 22/10/02)
